Also shows the early telegraph wires and a pole on the backbone route from the GPO to Parramatta.

&quot; The backbone of the public telegraph network was a route in George Street from the telegraph office to Redfern Station and a shared route along the railway line to Parramatta. By 1880 there were about 10 wires along George Street. This pole route appears from the General Post Office c.1890 on Arthur Streeton's 1893 painting of Redfern Station. From Redfern to Parramatta there were about 20 wires, and crossarms were used.  &quot;
- from <a href="http://www.telephonecollecting.org/lightpoles.htm" rel="nofollow">www.telephonecollecting.org/lightpoles.htm</a>
